membership:
Global Witness is a member of the Publish What You Pay coalition, a global network of civil society organisations that are united in their call for oil, gas and mining revenues to form the basis for development and improve the lives of citizens in resource-rich countries. PWYP undertakes public campaigns and policy advocacy to achieve disclosure of information about extractive industry revenues and contracts.&#xd;
&#xd;
Global Witness is a member of an informal coalition of Brussels based NGOs working on EU sustainable finance policy.&#xd;
&#xd;
Global Witness is also a coordinating committee member of the Financial Transparency Coalition - a consortium of Governments and NGOs - working together to address opacity in the international financial system, which creates inequalities that harm billions of people.&#xd;
&#xd;
Global Witness is also a member of an informal network of 65 NGOs working for strong conflict minerals regulation
